pageContext.claim: “More than half of America's counties report fewer than 20 cases last week. So, if you look at that, more than half of America's counties report fewer than 20 cases last week. ”
pageContext.analysis: Trump’s using numbers cleverly. While more than half of America’s counties did report fewer than 20 case, those counties also only house 10 percent of the country’s population. In other words, 90 percent of Americans were living in a county with more than 20 cover-19 cases.
